{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aee53f47-abd2-4f5e-a438-a4e43d3ef726","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_NgWHOAoZSs8gqqUYZ9ofjr","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing K8s crash dump config"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_3yAplzxW67foXliFeMY0hk","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"Reference check for .NET NativeAOT crash dump env vars\"","description":"Quick reference","initial_wait":5},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Quick reference"}],"interactionId":"65c69f3b-25ff-428e-b23b-bcf59ece364d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. I need to provide:\n\n1. The environment variables needed to configure .NET's crash dump collection\n2. The Kubernetes pod spec changes (volume mounts, etc.)\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables crash dump collection\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for the dump file\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpPath` - the directory where dumps are stored\n\nI should also mention `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` for additional diagnostics output if needed.\n\nFor .NET 5+ and NativeAOT in .NET 8+, these environment variables handle crash dump generation the same way. Now I'll put together a complete Kubernetes pod spec that configures these variables, sets up volume mounts for the dump directory, and shows how to collect the output.","outputTokens":615,"requestId":"CB0F:E6727:1EE3C4D:2229011:6A0529E9"},"id":"975add1d-ae2e-4c39-bfaf-4d366729d641","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:37.858Z","parentId":"bebde4c8-ddcf-41f9-8ff2-0404d959ee26"}
